quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  32,21,"And most surely We will make them taste a lesser punishment before the greater punishment, so that perhaps they may return to Us in repentance"
  32,22,"Who does greater wrong than someone who, when revelations of his Lord are recited to him, turns away from them? We shall inflict retribution on the guilty"
  32,23,"We gave Moses the Scripture, so [Muhammad] do not doubt that you are receiving it, just as We made it a guide for the Children of Israel"
  32,24,"We appointed leaders from among them, guiding by Our command when they were steadfast and when they had firm faith in Our signs"
  32,25,Surely your Lord will judge between them on the Day of Resurrection concerning that wherein they used to differ
  32,26,"Does it not guide them [to see] how many generations We destroyed before them, among whose ruined dwellings they now walk about? There truly are signs in this -- will they not listen"
  32,27,Have they not seen that We drive the water to the barren land and produce thereby crops of which their cattle and they themselves eat? Will they not then see
  32,28,"And they say, \"When will this judgement come, if you are telling the truth"
  32,29,"Say, \"On the Day of Judgement it will be of no benefit to those who were bent on denying the truth, if they [then] believe! They will be granted no respite"
  32,30,So turn away from them and wait. They too are waiting